quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  2,106,"We do not abrogate a verse or cause it to be forgotten except that We bring forth [one] better than it or similar to it. Do you not know that Allāh is over all things competent?"
  2,107,"Do you not know that to Allāh belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth and [that] you have not besides Allāh any protector or any helper?"
  2,108,"Or do you intend to ask{1} your Messenger as Moses was asked before? And whoever exchanges faith for disbelief has certainly strayed from the soundness of the way.",1:[i.e., persistently question or, as in the case of the disbelievers, demand a miracle of the Prophet (ﷺ) .]
  3,46,"He will speak to the people in the cradle and in maturity and will be of the righteous."
  3,47,"She said, "
  3,48,"And He will teach him writing and wisdom{1} and the Torah and the Gospel",1:[The teachings of the prophets.]
